Definition: a bluish-white lustrous metallic element
Example: brittle at ordinary temperatures but malleable when heated; used in a wide variety of alloys and in galvanizing iron; it occurs naturally as zinc sulphide in zinc blende
Synonyms: Zn, atomic_number_, metallic_element, a, bluish-white, lustrous, metallic, element, brittle, at, ordinary, temperatures, but, malleable, when, heated, used, in, wide, variety, of, alloys, and, galvanizing, iron, it, occurs, naturally, as, sulphide, blende
Category: noun.substance
